  "texts": [
    "Four monopole WiFi antennas (ANT-W63WS2-ccc) are placed therein in two pairs of parallel antennas separated by 9 cm, and the orientation of the two pairs is mutually orthogonal.",
    "These four antennas are connected to monomodal coaxial cables, such that the 4 × 4 scattering matrix S of our system is defined in an obvious manner.",
    "A four-port vector network analyzer (Rhode & Schwarz ZVA 67) is used to measure S (settings: 15 dBm emitted power, 1 kHz intermediate-frequency bandwidth).",
    "A programmable metasurface (detailed in the next subsection) covers parts of the cavity walls.",
    "Based on the decay rate of the inverse Fourier transform of transmission spectra measured between different pairs of ports and for different random metasurface configurations, we estimate the system's composite quality factor as Q = 620 57."
  ],
